        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it stay on if I move around in my sleep?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, aira was originally engineered for high-impact sport, so a side-sleeper isn't an issue. The most common cause of strips coming off is improper preparation: oily skin or skipping the 10-second press. Get those right and most wearers get at least a full 8 hours.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many tabs do I get per kit?",
            "answer": "<p>Your aira kit ships with the four strips plus 30 pairs of tabs, a full month of wear. Refill packs come in 30, 60, or 90 pairs, subscribe for a discount.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I reuse a tab if I take it off mid-night?",
            "answer": "<p>Once a tab leaves the skin its adhesive picks up oils and lint, which weakens the next stick. You can re-press a tab the same night if it lifts, but each pair is designed for a single use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there anything I shouldn't do before applying?",
            "answer": "<p>Skip moisturisers, oils, and serums on the bridge of the nose for at least 5 minutes before. Apply aira first, then your skincare around it.</p>"
          }
        }
